  "market_context": "EUR/USD is in a broader bearish expansion after a sharp drop from ~1.0920 to ~1.0530. The analyst drops to the hourly chart to find a positional short within the previous daily candle's EQ zone, where an opposing candle/order block sits as a PD array.",
  "key_observation": "At the 0.5 (EQ) of the previous daily range there is an opposing candle (order block) providing a protected high, allowing a positional short entry with stop above the high and target at the other side of the range for at least 2R.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Drop to the hourly chart and let the indicator plot the EQ of the previous higher time frame candle.",
    "Check the EQ zone for a PD array — identify an opposing candle / order block coinciding with the EQ, providing a protected high.",
    "Plan a positional short with stop above the opposing candle's high and target the other side of the range (≥ 2R).",
    "Watch price trade up into the opposing candle and confirm that the 0.5 of that candle is respected.",
    "Observe expansion lower, followed by retracement, then a new expansion using the series of up-close candles as the next reference.",
    "Confirm continuation as price trades through the prior low, validating the bearish bias for the next day."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade idea played out — price respected the opposing candle's 0.5, expanded lower, retraced, then made a new expansion through the low, reaching the other side of the range.",
  "lessons": "During expansion, up-close candles and the EQ of the prior higher time frame candle are respected; deep retracements into premium should not be expected. Pair the EQ with an opposing candle/order block to get a protected high for a high-probability positional short.",
